    <div id="content">
     <img alt="Bike Circle" src="img/bike_circle.jpg" style="float:right;margin:10px 20px;"/>
     <h2>
      Welcome to the Online Bicycle Education Program
     </h2>
     <p>
      Transportation and Parking Services (TAPS) and the Police Department have partnered
	in the development of this online training course for the safe operation
	of bicycles at the UC Davis campus.  Here you will learn about the traffic rules and
	regulations that apply to bicycle riders, and how to be a safe bicycle rider at UC Davis. The
	course will take approximately
      <strong>
       45 minutes
      </strong>
      to complete.
     </p>
     <p>
      <strong>
       If you have received a bicycle citation
      </strong>
      from the UC Davis Police Department,
	and the citation indicates that you may take this course for a fee, in lieu of paying the full
	citation amount, then you will be prompted for the citation number as part of the course.  After
	the course is over, you must follow the instructions for paying the course fee.  Unless the
	course is completed
      <strong>
       and
      </strong>
      paid for within 14 days of issue, the citation will be
	sent to the Yolo County Superior Court, and you will be required to attend your court hearing
	(or pay the full citation amount).
     </p>
     <p>
      <a data-role="button" href="auth/course/">
       Enter
      </a>
     </p>
